# Phase 17 — Unicode NFC normalization for Devanagari (सामान्यीकृत)

बताओ "== 1. precomposed vs decomposed compare equal after normalize =="
# "क़" written precomposed (U+0958) vs base क + nukta ़ (U+093C)
# In source, both forms normalize to the same NFC form at lex time, so two
# identifiers written differently refer to the SAME variable:
क़ है 42
बताओ क़                         # 42  (precomposed in this literal)

बताओ "== 2. सामान्यीकृत builtin returns NFC form =="
# A precomposed string normalized has length 2 (base + nukta) per nukta char
स है सामान्यीकृत("क़")
बताओ स.लम्बाई()                 # 2 — decomposed to क + ़
जाँचो स.लम्बाई() बराबर 2, "NFC लम्बाई गलत"

बताओ "== 3. plain text unchanged =="
जाँचो सामान्यीकृत("नमस्ते") बराबर "नमस्ते", "plain बदल गया"

बताओ "== 4. equality after normalize =="
# normalize both forms → equal
जाँचो सामान्यीकृत("ड़") बराबर सामान्यीकृत("ड़"), "norm-eq गलत"

बताओ ""
बताओ "सब परीक्षण पास ✓"
